 :tx/rationale "ROOT CAUSE FOUND: has_new_external_txns() in LiveStore is permanently false once all 256 shard directories exist. It checks txns/ directory mtime, but on Linux, creating a file in txns/ab/ changes txns/ab/'s mtime, NOT txns/'s mtime. Once all shards exist (which happens early in the store's lifecycle — currently 257 shard dirs), the txns/ mtime NEVER changes from new writes. This means: (1) The defensive flush guard in flush() (INV-STORE-022 fix from commit 1649a4e4) NEVER fires. (2) Every LiveStore::drop() writes store.bin unconditionally. (3) When multiple LiveStores overlap (main.rs + command), the last to drop wins the cache write. (4) If the last-to-drop LiveStore has STALE state (loaded before the other wrote), its stale state overwrites the correct cache. (5) The next reader loads the stale cache, missing the intermediate writes. The writes are NOT lost (EDN txn files are durable per C1), but the cache is stale until a fingerprint mismatch triggers a full rebuild. VERIFIED: txns/ mtime unchanged after write_tx to existing shard. 257 shard directories confirmed."
